  "faq01Q": "What is YARA?",
  "@faq01Q": {
    "description": "faq01Q"
  },
  "faq01A": "YARA is a pattern-matching tool used to identify malware based on textual or binary patterns. MentoringProtector uses YARA rules as one of its detection engines alongside signatures and heuristics.",
  "@faq01A": {
    "description": "faq01A"
  },
  "faq02Q": "Why does MentoringProtector need administrator rights?",
  "@faq02Q": {
    "description": "faq02Q"
  },
  "faq02A": "The main application runs without admin rights. Administrator access (UAC) is only requested when you click 'Fix automatically' in Vulnerability Scanner - this is required to modify Windows system registry settings.",
  "@faq02A": {
    "description": "faq02A"
  },
  "faq03Q": "What is Smart Scan Cache?",
  "@faq03Q": {
    "description": "faq03Q"
  },
  "faq03A": "Smart Scan Cache stores hash-based scan results so files that haven't changed don't need to be rescanned. This makes repeated scans significantly faster without compromising security.",
  "@faq03A": {
    "description": "faq03A"
  },
  "faq04Q": "What is the Bloom Filter used for?",
  "@faq04Q": {
    "description": "faq04Q"
  },
  "faq04A": "The Bloom Filter is a probabilistic data structure used for fast phishing domain lookups in Web Protection. It checks ~100K domains in microseconds with near-zero false negatives.",
  "@faq04A": {
    "description": "faq04A"
  },
  "faq05Q": "What happens to files in Quarantine?",
  "@faq05Q": {
    "description": "faq05Q"
  },
  "faq05A": "Quarantined files are encrypted with AES-256 and stored in a protected folder. They cannot execute. You can restore them if they were detected as false positives, or permanently delete them.",
  "@faq05A": {
    "description": "faq05A"
  },
  "faq06Q": "How does the heuristic engine work?",
  "@faq06Q": {
    "description": "faq06Q"
  },
  "faq06A": "The heuristic engine analyzes PE file structure: imports, suspicious strings, entropy (packed/encrypted sections), digital signature validity, and file size anomalies - without needing a signature database.",
  "@faq06A": {
    "description": "faq06A"
  },
  "faq07Q": "What is ETW monitoring?",
  "@faq07Q": {
    "description": "faq07Q"
  },
  "faq07A": "Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) is a kernel-level logging mechanism. MentoringProtector uses it to detect DLL injection and suspicious process activity at the OS kernel level.",
  "@faq07A": {
    "description": "faq07A"
  },
  "faq08Q": "Why choose MentoringProtector over Windows Defender?",
  "@faq08Q": {
    "description": "faq08Q"
  },
  "faq08A": "MentoringProtector is an educational platform: it explains WHY a file is suspicious (explainable detection), teaches cyber hygiene habits, and shows you exactly what detection logic triggered. Defender is great protection but doesn't teach.",
  "@faq08A": {
    "description": "faq08A"
  },
